<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="389" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="389">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="389">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="389">Adult male.</emphasis>
General color of the body light brown. Length of the forewings: 6.3 mm (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="389">n</emphasis>
= 1). Coloration of the forewings similar to the body, with a subapical transverse, sinuous, white stripe, and a white, rectangular spot at midlength of the costal margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="389">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="389">Head</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Heads in dorsal view of the species of the Smicridea brasiliana group A Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) brasiliana B S. (R.) weidneri C S. (R.) vermiculata D S. (R.) atrobasis E S. (R.) nanda. Abbreviations: CSL length of the coronal suture, IOD interocular distance, MEW maximum eye width, MHW maximum head width. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.80961.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/712814" pageId="0" pageNumber="389">1A</figureCitation>
). In dorsal view rectangular, transverse. Mesal margins of the eyes, in dorsal view, parallel, postgenal areas reduced. Interocular area rectangular, wider than long. Interocular distance 2.2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
shorter than MHW. Coronal suture 2/3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
shorter than IOD. Eyes lightly produced anteriorly, maximum eye width 3.3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
shorter than MHW. Anterolateral setose warts present, subtriangular, bifid posteriorly, mesal lobe shorter than the lateral. Posterior setose warts subtriangular. Maxillary palps missing.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="389">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="389">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="389">Male genitalia</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Anterolateral margin of segment IX rounded and produced (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Male genitalia of Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) brasiliana A segments IX, X, inferior appendages and phallus, lateral view B segments IX, X and inferior appendages, dorsal view C tip of the phallus, lateral view (lateral spines removed) D tip of the phallus, dorsal view E tip of the phallus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.80961.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/712816" pageId="0" pageNumber="389">3A</figureCitation>
). Tergum of segment X triangular in lateral view, apex rounded, dorsal and ventral margins straight, the ventral one with a sclerotized H-shaped area directed anteriorly through segment IX (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Male genitalia of Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) brasiliana A segments IX, X, inferior appendages and phallus, lateral view B segments IX, X and inferior appendages, dorsal view C tip of the phallus, lateral view (lateral spines removed) D tip of the phallus, dorsal view E tip of the phallus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.80961.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/712816" pageId="0" pageNumber="389">3A</figureCitation>
); in dorsal view divided mesally into two subtriangular hemitergites with apex subacute; internal margin of each hemitergite straight, with a concavity subapically (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Male genitalia of Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) brasiliana A segments IX, X, inferior appendages and phallus, lateral view B segments IX, X and inferior appendages, dorsal view C tip of the phallus, lateral view (lateral spines removed) D tip of the phallus, dorsal view E tip of the phallus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.80961.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/712816" pageId="0" pageNumber="389">3A, B</figureCitation>
). Inferior appendages with two articules, setose, curved mesally in dorsal view; basal article narrow for a short distance proximally, from where it widens to the apex; apical article narrow, short, with rounded apex (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Male genitalia of Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) brasiliana A segments IX, X, inferior appendages and phallus, lateral view B segments IX, X and inferior appendages, dorsal view C tip of the phallus, lateral view (lateral spines removed) D tip of the phallus, dorsal view E tip of the phallus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.80961.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/712816" pageId="0" pageNumber="389">3B</figureCitation>
). Phallus with long and tubular phallobase; basal portion broad, forming an angle of ~ 90° with distal part, which is slightly curved and with widened apex (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Male genitalia of Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) brasiliana A segments IX, X, inferior appendages and phallus, lateral view B segments IX, X and inferior appendages, dorsal view C tip of the phallus, lateral view (lateral spines removed) D tip of the phallus, dorsal view E tip of the phallus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.80961.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/712816" pageId="0" pageNumber="389">3A, C</figureCitation>
); dorsal periphallic cap present subapically; apex of the phallus with a row of small spines extending from one side to the other ventrally, in dorsal view slightly produced laterally (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Male genitalia of Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) brasiliana A segments IX, X, inferior appendages and phallus, lateral view B segments IX, X and inferior appendages, dorsal view C tip of the phallus, lateral view (lateral spines removed) D tip of the phallus, dorsal view E tip of the phallus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.80961.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/712816" pageId="0" pageNumber="389">3A, C-E</figureCitation>
). Internal sclerotized section of ejaculatory duct long and straight in lateral view (~ 2/3 the phallobase length), in dorsal view longitudinally divided in two (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Male genitalia of Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) brasiliana A segments IX, X, inferior appendages and phallus, lateral view B segments IX, X and inferior appendages, dorsal view C tip of the phallus, lateral view (lateral spines removed) D tip of the phallus, dorsal view E tip of the phallus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.80961.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/712816" pageId="0" pageNumber="389">3E</figureCitation>
); distal end with an elongate, pointed dorsal plate, that bends upwards, then ventrad to the left at mid-length and upwards again, ending slightly beyond the tip of the ejaculatory duct; basally this plate bears a lateral spine; ventrally to the ejaculatory duct there are two spine-like plates and two lateroventral subrectangular plates that narrow posteriorly ending in a point (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Male genitalia of Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) brasiliana A segments IX, X, inferior appendages and phallus, lateral view B segments IX, X and inferior appendages, dorsal view C tip of the phallus, lateral view (lateral spines removed) D tip of the phallus, dorsal view E tip of the phallus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.80961.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/712816" pageId="0" pageNumber="389">3C-E</figureCitation>
). Endotheca simple.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.80961.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/712816" pageId="0" pageNumber="389" start="Figure 3" startId="F3">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="389">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="389">Figure 3.</emphasis>
Male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ulmer" baseAuthorityYear="1905" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Smicridea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) brasiliana" order="Trichoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brasiliana" subGenus="Rhyacophylax">Smicridea (Rhyacophylax) brasiliana</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="389">A</emphasis>
segments IX, X, inferior appendages and phallus, lateral view 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="389">B</emphasis>
segments IX, X and inferior appendages, dorsal view 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="389">C</emphasis>
tip of the phallus, lateral view (lateral spines removed) 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="389">D</emphasis>
